{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:proverbs.15",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 15,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 15",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 15 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.15.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 15:1",
      "text": "Anger slays even wise men; yet a submissive answer turns away wrath: but a grievous word stirs up anger.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.15.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 15:2",
      "text": "The tongue of the wise knows what is good: but the mouth of the foolish tells out evil things.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.15.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 15:3",
      "text": "The eyes of the Lord behold both the evil and the good in every place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.15.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 15:4",
      "text": "The wholesome tongue is a tree of life, and he that keeps it shall be filled with",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.15.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 15:5",
      "text": "A fool scorns his father's instruction: but he that keeps his commandments is more prudent. In abounding righteousness is great strength: but the ungodly shall",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.15.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 15:6",
      "text": "In the houses of the righteous is much strength: but the fruits of the ungodly shall perish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.15.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 15:7",
      "text": "The lips of the wise are bound by discretion: but the hearts of the foolish are not safe.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.15.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 15:8",
      "text": "The sacrifices of the ungodly are an abomination to the Lord; but the prayers of them that walk honestly are acceptable with him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.15.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 15:9",
      "text": "The ways of an ungodly man are an abomination to the Lord; but he loves those that follow after righteousness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.15.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 15:10",
      "text": "The instruction of the simple is known by them that pass by; but they that hate reproofs die disgracefully.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.15.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 15:11",
      "text": "Hell and destruction are manifest to the Lord; how shall not also be the hearts of men?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.15.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 15:12",
      "text": "An uninstructed person will not love those that reprove him; neither will he associate with the wise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.15.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 15:13",
      "text": "When the heart rejoices the countenance is cheerful; but when it is in sorrow, the countenance is sad.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.15.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 15:14",
      "text": "An upright heart seeks discretion; but the mouth of the uninstructed will experience evils.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.15.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 15:15",
      "text": "The eyes of the wicked are always looking for evil things; but the good are always quiet.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.15.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 15:16",
      "text": "Better is a small portion with the fear of the Lord, than great treasures without the fear of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.15.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 15:17",
      "text": "Better is an entertainment of herbs with friendliness and kindness, than a feast of calves, with enmity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.15.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 15:18",
      "text": "A passionate man stirs up strife; but he that is slow to anger appeases even a",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.15.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 15:19",
      "text": "The ways of sluggards are strewn with thorns; but those of the diligent are made smooth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.15.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 15:20",
      "text": "A wise son gladdens his father; but a foolish son sneers at his mother.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.15.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 15:21",
      "text": "The ways of a foolish man are void of sense; but a wise man proceeds on his way aright.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.15.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 15:22",
      "text": "They that honour not councils put off deliberation; but counsel abides in the hearts of counsellors.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.15.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 15:23",
      "text": "A bad man will by no means attend to counsel; neither will he say anything seasonable, or good for the common weal.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.15.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 15:24",
      "text": "The thoughts of the wise are ways of life, that he may turn aside and escape from hell.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.15.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 15:25",
      "text": "The Lord pulls down the houses of scorners; but he establishes the border of the widow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.15.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 15:26",
      "text": "An unrighteous thought is abomination to the Lord; but the sayings of the pure are held in honour.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.15.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 15:27",
      "text": "A receiver of bribes destroys himself; but he that hates the receiving of bribes is safe. 27a [By alms and by faithful dealings sins are purged away;] but by the fear of the Lord every one departs from evil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.15.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 15:28",
      "text": "The hearts of the righteous meditate faithfulness; but the mouth of the ungodly answers evil things. 28a The ways of righteous men are acceptable with the Lord; and through them even enemies become friends.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.15.29",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 15:29",
      "text": "God is far from the ungodly; but he hearkens to the prayers of the righteous. 29a Better are small receipts with righteousness, than abundant fruits with unrighteousness. 29b Let the heart of a man think justly, that his steps may be rightly ordered of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.15.30",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 15:30",
      "text": "The eye that sees rightly rejoices the heart; and a good report fattens the bones.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.15.32",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 15:32",
      "text": "He that rejects instruction hates himself; but he that minds reproofs loves his soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.15.33",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 15:33",
      "text": "The fear of the Lord is instruction and wisdom; and the highest honour will correspond therewith.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
